    <title>Tomato Rasam Recipe</title>

	<link href="~/css/rasam.css" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>

 
    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>🍅 Tomato Rasam</h1>
       
        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>3 Ripe Tomatoes (Chopped)</li>
            <li>1/2 cup Tamarind Extract</li>
            <li>1 tsp Black Pepper (Crushed)</li>
            <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp Turmeric Powder</li>
            <li>2 tsp Rasam Powder</li>
            <li>2 cups Water</li>
            <li>2 tsp Ghee</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp Mustard Seeds</li>
            <li>2 Dry Red Chilies</li>
            <li>Curry Leaves (Few)</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Coriander Leaves (Chopped)</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Boil tomatoes in 2 cups of water until soft.</li>
            <li>Mash the tomatoes and add tamarind extract, turmeric, rasam powder, salt, and pepper.</li>
            <li>Simmer for 5-7 minutes until well combined.</li>
            <li>In another pan, heat ghee, add mustard seeds, cumin, red chilies, and curry leaves.</li>
            <li>Pour the tempering over the rasam.</li>
            <li>Garnish with coriander leaves and serve hot.</li>
            <li>Enjoy with steamed rice or as a soup!</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
